344 OARTAE MISCELLANEAE.

CCCXXIX. Grift of the state office and chaplainry called the Bedalry of the choir of Brechin, vacant by the expiry of the last gift- thereos, to Mathew Lockie lawful son to Quhintene Lokkie burgess of Edinburgh, for his support at the schools during the space of seven years. Dated at Halieruidhous 20 May 1583.
